messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /v1/posts/{post}

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- HEAD:
  false

- POST:
  false

- OPTIONS:
  false

- TRACE:
  false

- GET:
  true

- PUT:
  true

- DELETE:
  true

- PATCH:
  true

Explanation:
- routes/api.php wraps routes in Route::prefix('v1')->group(...), so the resource paths are prefixed with "v1" => base /v1.
- The PostController routes are declared twice (in different route groups):
  - Inside the authenticated middleware group:
    Route::apiResource('posts', PostController::class)->only(['update', 'store', 'destroy']);
    This creates:
      - PUT /posts/{post} and PATCH /posts/{post} (update)
      - DELETE /posts/{post} (destroy)
      - POST /posts (store) â€” NOTE: this is for /v1/posts (no {post})
  - Outside the middleware group:
    Route::apiResource('posts', PostController::class)->only(['index', 'show']);
    This creates:
      - GET /posts (index)
      - GET /posts/{post} (show)
- Combining the above for the same path /v1/posts/{post] yields explicit routes for GET, PUT, PATCH and DELETE.
- The DELETE route corresponds to App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostController@destroy.
- HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE and POST are not explicitly registered for /v1/posts/{post} in the provided route definitions. (Per your instruction, I have not assumed implicit framework behaviors such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling.)
